"Dear customers,
Thank you for purchasing and using this device. Before activating the 'Amateur Channel', 'Custom Channel' and 'Repeater List', please read the following carefully as to thoroughly understand the statement. You may choose not to use the three modes, but if you press to confirm, it would be considered as approval of the entire content of this statement.
According to Regulation on Radio Frequency Division of the People’s Republic of China, amateur service is referred to as radio communication service for amateur radio hobbyists to have self-training, inter-communication and technology research. Amateur radio hobbyists are those who are interested in radio technology and have been officially approved, with this interest being simply a personal hobby and not for profit.
The frequency bands of 'Amateur Channel', 'Custom Channel' and 'Repeater List' of this device belongs to amateur service frequency bands. Activation of the Three modes will enable this device to conduct services on the amateur frequency bands.
According to the Management of Amateur Radio Stations, the device that conducts amateur services is defined as an amateur radio station, for which the setting up requires legal approval as well as the amateur radio station license.
Before activating the 'Amateur Channel', 'Custom Channel' and 'Repeater List', please first ensure that you have the relevant qualifications and have been officially approved.
According to Management of Amateur Radio Stations, setting up an amateur radio station requires a couple of prerequisites as followed:
(1) Be well aware of the regulations on radio management;
(2) Have the technical and operational skills required by national radio regulatory agencies;
(3) The radio transmission device meets China’s technical standards on radio management;
(4) Other relevant requirements regulated by law and administrative regulations;
For departments applying for setting up an amateur radio station, the person in charge of the station should meet requirement （1）, and the technical director should meet both requirements (1) and (2).
Individuals applying for setting up an amateur radio station with transmission functions must be over 18 years old. Meanwhile, the setting up of a space amateur radio station should comply with Management of Amateur Radio Stations, or relevant regulations on space radio station management.
If you have met the requirements of setting up the amateur radio station and have legally gone through the approval process, the following requirements need to be met as you are using the amateur radio station.
(5) Be well aware of the regulations on radio management;
(6) Have the technical and operational skills required by the national radio agency and have obtained the certificate of relevant operational skills;
According to Management of Amateur Radio Stations, when the amateur service and/or amateur-satellite service use the frequency as secondary service, or share any frequency with other main services, they should obey the radio regulations in terms of using this frequency. Amateur radio stations enjoy equal rights in using the frequency within the permitted frequency bands. In addition, do not maliciously occupy the frequency and/or interfere with other users in service.
According to Management of Amateur Radio Stations, the communication object of amateur radio stations should be limited to amateur radio stations.
During emergencies such as catastrophic natural disasters, amateur radio stations are allowed to make communication with non-amateur radio stations under the premises of making a timely report to local radio management institutions; the communication content should be limited to either urgent matters directly related to rescue and relief work, or missions assigned by emergency rescue departments. Without permission of local radio management institutions, amateur radio stations are not allowed to broadcast or collectively transmit any signals in any form.
During communication, amateur radio stations should use plain language or abbreviations, simplified words accepted in the amateur radio field. The data file should be exchanged in a public way. To experiment a new coding system, modulation type and/or digital communication protocol, the amateur radio station should make it public in advance and submit relevant technical information to local radio management institution.
The founder of an amateur radio station should effectively monitor the transmission device to ensure its correct functioning and that any harmful interference caused by the transmission device can be ceased.
If the legally set communication scope involves more than two provinces, municipalities, municipalities directly under the central government, or amateur radio stations abroad, the nonlocal transmission can be operated outside the setting location, but it should obey relevant regulations of the local radio management institutions.
Amateur radio stations are not allowed to transmit or receive signals irrelevant with amateur services or satellite amateur services. They are not allowed to disseminate or publish the non-amateur or non-satellite-amateur signals that are received by accident. Amateur radio stations are used by its founder and users for inter-communication, technology research and self-training.
Management of Amateur Radio Stations prohibits amateur radio stations from working on the following activities:
(1) Publishing, disseminating information that is against law or public morality;
(2) Working on commercial or other activities that involve making profit;
(3) Impeding communication between other amateur radio stations;
(4) Other activities which are prohibited by law and administrative regulations.
According to Management of Amateur Radio Stations, as the founder and user of an amateur radio station, you should abide by the following rules:
(1) Strengthen self-discipline and accept the guidance, supervision, and examination of radio management institutions or their entrusted parties. Critical data should be logged such as duration, frequency, mode, contact for each communication, the log should be reserved for two years for examination of radio management institutions.
(2) Properly use the call sign. The amateur radio station should initiate transmitting its call sign each time it sets up or ends a communication; the call sign should be transmitted for at least one time in every ten minutes during transmission. For transmission operated on other amateur radio stations, or nonlocal transmission operated in places outside the setting location permitted by national radio regulatory agencies, the amateur call sign should be used as per Amateur Radio Station Call Sign Instructions attached to Management of Amateur Radio Stations. It is prohibited to embezzle, transfer, privately make up, or illegally use the amateur radio station call sign.
(3) Cooperate with radio management institutions to implement supervision and examination on the amateur radio station.
According to Article 43 of Radio Regulations of the People’s Republic of China, the radio management institutions have the right to impose punishment for the following behaviors:
(1) Arbitrarily setting up and using an amateur radio station without written permission of official institutions;
(2) Interfering with other legitimate radio services;
(3) Casually changing ratified cases and/or items of a radio device to transmit, receive signals that are irrelevant with amateur services or satellite amateur services.
For any of the following behaviors, radio management institutions may order you to make corrections within a time limit, and issue a warning or impose a penalty below 30,000 RMB.
(1) Altering, copying, or forging an amateur radio station license, or reselling, renting, lending and illegally transferring an amateur radio station license in other forms;
(2) Embezzling, renting, lending, transferring, or privately making up or illegally using a call sign;
(3) Illegally using the amateur radio station which leads to serious consequences;
(4) Obtaining an amateur radio station license improperly;
(5) Continue using an amateur radio station after expiration date for setting up or using the station;
(6) Hiding relevant circumstances from the radio management institutions, providing false materials or refusing to provide veritable materials that truly reflect your radio activities.
(7) Using frequencies that are out of the ratified scope or other behaviors that are against regulations on frequency management.
Lastly, please let us remind you for the last time, before activating the 'Amateur Channel', 'Custom Channel' and 'Repeater List', make sure that you have all the relevant qualifications and are well aware of correlative laws and statutes including but not limited to Radio Regulations of the People’s Republic of China, Management of Amateur Radio Stations. Please use the device in a legal and civilized manner. For any consequences led by illegal activation of the 'Amateur Channel', 'Custom Channel' and 'Repeater List', the manufacturer shall assume no responsibility.
